GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 943
Short Title: Kids Over Corporations Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Chitlik, Murdock, and Smith (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
April 30, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT REPEALING THE SCHEDULED PHASEOUT OF THE CORPORATE INCOME
3 TAX AND SETTING THE CORPORATE INCOME TAX RATE AT FIVE PERCENT.
4 Whereas, North Carolina law currently phases out the corporate income tax entirely,
5 reducing the rate to zero in future years; and
6 Whereas, eliminating the corporate income tax would significantly reduce the State's
7 long-term revenue capacity and shift the responsibility for funding public services onto
8 individuals and families; and
9 Whereas, North Carolina's current corporate income tax rate is already significantly
10 lower than that of neighboring states; and
11 Whereas, a balanced tax system requires that corporations benefiting from North
12 Carolina's workforce, infrastructure, and public systems contribute to their maintenance; and
13 Whereas, sustained investment in public education and workforce development is
14 essential to the State's economic competitiveness; Now, therefore,
15 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
16 SECTION 1. G.S. 105-130.3 reads as rewritten:
17 "§ 105-130.3. Corporations.
18 A tax is imposed on the State net income of every C Corporation doing business in this State.
19 State at the rate of five percent (5%). An S Corporation is not subject to the tax levied in this
20 section. The tax is a percentage of the taxpayer's State net income computed as follows:
21 Taxable Years Beginning Tax
22 In 2025 2.25%
23 In 2026 2%
24 In 2028 1%
25 After 2029 0%."
26 SECTION 2. This act is effective for taxable years beginning on or after January 1,
27 2026.
*S943-v-1*

